It's #SpotlightSaturday and this is a record setting edition! 

Bravo Zulu to eight #USCG rescue swimmers who recently earned the @guinnessworldrecords for climbing the 29,028 foot height of Mt. Everest at Air Station Cape Cod. The crew completed the climb in 1 hour, 26 minutes and 20 seconds beating the prior record held by eight Royal Air Force firefighters by 30 minutes.

node.text: It's #SpotlightSaturday! #BravoZulu to Lieutenant Commander (LCDR) Amanda Le Monde, the executive officer at the Coast Guard Pacific Strike Team, on being selected as the 2020 International Association of Emergency Managers Uniformed Emergency Manager of the Year! node.text:
Lieutenant (Lt.) Jessica Shafer is one of only 14 women to become a Surfman in the #CoastGuard and became the first female commanding officer of Coast Guard Station Cape Disappointment in 2018, 141 years after the station first opened. Lt. Shafer is an elite lifeboat pilot, having earned coxswain, heavy weather coxswain, tactical coxswain and surfman qualifications, as well as multiple boarding officer certifications.

Lt. Shafer on why she joined the #USCG: “The benefits were unbelievable...so that was the appeal, plus the outdoors, and the physical nature of it. Seeing the country, and serving the country. Volunteerism was a big part of it also. I wanted to be in a job where people wanted to be there.” #GoCoastGuard #SemperParatus #CareerGoals #MilitaryCareer #WomensHistoryMonth #militarywomen #whyjoin #notyouraveragejob #USA 🇺🇸⚓️

We are not throwin' away OUR shot!

Just Cheyenne, this cutter is pretty awesome!⁠
⁠
The #USCG Cutter Cheyenne (WLR 75405) is a 75-foot river buoy tender homeported in St. Louis, MO. The Coast Guard operates 18 tenders of 75-foot and 65-foot lengths on rivers in the western United States, deploying ATON buoys and day boards to mark river channels and to ease the efficient flow of commerce.⁠
